1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with breast cancer grading of histological images using deep learning methods, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a semi-supervised framework based on expectation maximization (EM) model, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning methods to automatically grade breast cancer, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.DL (Deep Learning): The paper leverages unannotated datasets to enhance the trained model, which is a common technique in deep learning. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses collaborative filtering method to extract useful and credible datasets from the unannotated images, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval.
